      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, you just said to take \"slightly higher\" rapid acting because i ate less? that makes no sense at all. if i didn't eat carbs, shouldn't i need LESS insulin, not more? i'm worried if i follow what you're saying i'll end up in the ER with hypoglycemia. just give it to me straight—should i just take my normal basal dose and call it a night or is there a specific amount of rapid acting i should be using to stay safe?",
